Löffingen: Köpfler still single candidate
Information on the Internet: although the Baarstädtchen Löffingen with its 7514 inhabitants, an intact infrastructure, a future-oriented school, children, youth and the elderly policy, as well as its own city can be described as an attractive town, has not yet reported second mayor candidate.
As the only candidate for the succession of age reasons no longer ran mayor Norbert Brugger is the 46-year-old bank clerk and host Dieter Köpfler from Löffingen.
The application deadline expires on Monday, November 11 at 6 pm.
